The paper deals with information flow in distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of channels and messages suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. The introduction of a new formalization of partial disclosure and the compositional principle suggest that the paper may also be relevant to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
